I am writing about a property in {{ county_name }} County, Ohio that may have generated excess proceeds after a tax foreclosure or forfeited land sale. Excess proceeds are the funds remaining after the county applies the sale proceeds to delinquent taxes, penalties, costs, and other amounts allowed by law. Those funds are held by the County Treasurer until someone with a valid claim comes forward.

